title: Update the firefox extension using own self-distribution website is not working.
content:
We have our own website for self-distribution of our extension called "Crypto Web Extension" (https://download.tescosw.cz/crypto/). A few days ago, I used the API to create a signed XPI file for a new version of this extension, which I uploaded to our self-distribution website as usual. However, when checking the update of this extension in Firefox, I found that the update to a newer version of the extension does not work. I checked everything on our side and everything seems to be fine. So could someone please help me? I suspect that there may be a problem with the Firefox browser itself.

TestCase (see also attached gif): 1. Open Firefox browser. 2. From the address https://download.tescosw.cz/crypto/dev/, install the "Crypto Web Extension" extension with older version number 24.02.9054 in the Firefox browser. This is a previously released version of the extension, which is available for testing purposes only on this development part of the website. 3. Then click "Check for Updates" in the extension management. 4. Then click "Update". The extension should be updated from the production address https://download.tescosw.cz/crypto/ to the newer version number 25.02.9265, due to the set json file at https://download.tescosw.cz/crypto/files/firefox_updates.json. However, after clicking "Update", the extension does not update to the newer version. However, if I remove the older version of the extension from Firefox and then try to install the new version of the add-on from the production address https://download.tescosw.cz/crypto/, it works fine.

Can someone please look at this problem and check if there is a bug in the Firefox browser? This worked as late as October of last year, 2024.

I have the latest version of Firefox browser 138.0.3

Thank you!

Merhabalar, önceden Google Chrome kullanıyordum sonrasında bazı sevmediğim politikalarından dolayı son 2 yıldır Firefox kullanmaktayım. Tarayıcıdan genel anlamda memnunum fakat öyle bir eksiklik var ki insanı çileden çıkartan cinsten.

Şöyle ki; Whatsapp, internet veya forum herhangi bir yerden fotoğrafı kaydetmek veya whatsapptan birine göndermek istediğimde Google Chrome'da sürükle - bırak yöntemi ile masaüstüne veya whatsapp'ta bir kişiye gönderebiliyorum fakat Firefox'ta bunu yapamıyorum, masaüstüne "blob_https...." diye kaydediyor ve hiç bir işimize yaramıyor, illa ki sağ tıkla - farklı kaydet - masaüstü - kaydet sonrasında göndereceğin yerde tam tersi olay.

Sürükle bırak yöntemini kullanamamamız kullanıcı deneyimini ciddi şekilde baltalamakta ve gerçekten fotoğraflarla uğraşan kişiler için işkence. İşin açıkçası farklı tarayıcılara bile dönmeyi düşünmedim değil. Bunun herhangi bir çözümü var mı? Veya güncelleme ile eklenecek bir şey mi?

Menemukan dan meminum pil aborsi untuk mengakhiri kehamilan tanpa bantuan dokter atau perawat disebut “aborsi yang dikelola sendiri” (yang oleh sebagian orang disebut sebagai “aborsi di rumah”). Penelitian menunjukkan bahwa melakukan aborsi sendiri dengan pil aborsi (mifepristone dan/atau misoprostol) aman dan efektif

Ada dua cara berbeda untuk melakukan aborsi dengan obat: Menggunakan 2 obat berbeda untuk mengakhiri kehamilan Anda: mifepristone dan misoprostol. Hanya menggunakan misoprostol untuk mengakhiri kehamilan Anda Halaman ini membahas tentang melakukan aborsi hanya dengan menggunakan misoprostol – aman, efektif, dan legal untuk digunakan di negara-negara yang melegalkan aborsi. Ini bekerja 85-95% sepanjang waktu dan dapat digunakan hingga 11 minggu sejak hari pertama menstruasi terakhir Anda.

ABORSI MEDIS TERBAIK No.1 Aborsi medis adalah aborsi yang dilakukan dengan menggunakan kombinasi obat-obatan baik yang diminum secara oral atau melalui vagina. Ia bekerja dengan menghentikan pertumbuhan kehamilan dan kemudian menyebabkan lapisan rahim meluruh. Aborsi jenis ini dapat dilakukan segera setelah kehamilan dimulai hingga sekitar usia kehamilan sembilan minggu.

APA ITU ABORSI MEDIS? Aborsi medis (atau aborsi obat) adalah prosedur di mana pengobatan (obat resep) digunakan untuk mengakhiri kehamilan. Tindakan ini tidak memerlukan pembedahan dan dilakukan hingga minggu kesembilan kehamilan. Ini melibatkan penggunaan dua obat – mifepristone dan misoprostol. Mifepristone bekerja dengan cara memblokir hormon progesteron. Tanpa progesteron, kehamilan tidak dapat terus berkembang di dalam rahim. Misoprostol menyebabkan kram dan pendarahan saat mengosongkan rahim.

KAPAN SESEORANG BISA MELAKUKAN ABORSI MEDIS??? Aborsi medis dilakukan hingga sekitar sembilan minggu kehamilan. Hal ini dapat dilakukan segera setelah Anda mengetahui bahwa Anda hamil. Penyedia layanan kesehatan Anda akan menggunakan USG untuk memastikan Anda hamil dan berapa lama Anda hamil. Jika usia kehamilan Anda sudah melebihi sembilan minggu, ada pilihan lain untuk mengakhiri kehamilan. Penyedia layanan kesehatan Anda dapat berbicara dengan Anda tentang pilihan lain dan membantu Anda memutuskan mana yang terbaik untuk Anda.

MANFAAT ABORSI MEDIS? Anda bisa mendapatkannya segera setelah Anda tahu Anda hamil. Tidak ada operasi atau anestesi yang terlibat. Anda bisa berada di rumah setelah kram dan pendarahan terjadi. Ini mungkin terasa lebih alami. Anda dapat memiliki sistem pendukung bersama Anda.

title: FF has "looping" issue within a modem console, Opera doesn't.
content:
Running FF115.23.1ESR on a Win7/32 box I use in network maintenance/configuration.

If I log into the modem main page and select from the side-bar menu, FF drops me back to the modem's login screen (Grounghog Day style). This behaviour is repeatable (endlessly) on:

  • * another identical modem (same/latest firmware). These have repeatedly been factory reset and firmware reloaded. No change.
  • * another Win7 box (/64) on same FF release.

Opera - reluctantly added on those same Win7 boxes - does not have this (mis-)behaviour.

Win10/64 running FF138.0.4 does not have this issue.

Up until about ten weeks back, the (then-current) Win7/X esr release did NOT have this problem.

Yes, I HAVE cleared cache/cookies repeatedly before sessions, to no avail. <><><><><><><><><><><><><><><><><><><><><><><><><><><><> [EDIT:] The on-line modem/router emulator can be accessed at https://support.netcommwireless.com/e.../login.html The default un/pswd is admin/admin. Once in the main page, select "Advanced" from the left menu list. This (in the emulator) opens the Advanced page, as it should. In a normal situation here, it simply reverts to the login page.

Q1: Anyone have any experience like this, or any clues/suggestions?

Q2: To continue using these Win7 boxes in that role, am I forced to abandon FF?

title: Can't pin or remove extension tools from the toolbar.
content:
I am currently running version 138.0.4 (64 bit). I have not been able to add any extension's tool to the toolbar. It used to be that a left-click on the "Extensions" tool produced a drop down window with a list of installed extensions and the option to and/remove any extension from the toolbar. Things still work this way with Microsoft Edge (Chromium) and Google Chrome. Left-clicking the new Firefox "unified extensions tool" opens an Add-ons Manager with "Recommendations", "Extensions", "Themes" and "Plugins". Clicking on "Extensions" does list the extensions I have installed, but there is no way to add the tools for those extensions to the toolbar.

Please, please, please put to original "Extensions" tool back on the toolbar. If you must add a tool to the toolbar for the "Add-ons Manager", do it. I actually think that would be a very good idea. Call the tool "Add-ons Manager", NOT "Extensions"!

NOTE: the computer I am running Firefox on in this instance does have my desired tools in the toolbar. I installed Firefox on this machine long before the newer versions of Firefox were released. I have used Firefox for years as my default browser on several computers over the years.

Thank you, William A. Butcher
